snippet.title: Zombie Nation (NES) Playthrough - NintendoComplete
snippet.description:
A beginning to end playthrough of Meldac's 1991 NES game, Zombie Nation.

I really love the hysterically overblown rendition of the Star Spangled Banner, blasted with the most obnoxious combo of digital samples imaginable. The vomit and eyeballs used as weapons from the severed zombie head are pretty neat, too. It's too bad that the controls suck so badly, but then, it seems to go along just fine next to the haminess of everything else!

This is a video that I uploaded a few years ago but the upload was locked at a lousy 240p. I found an old hard drive with my original source files, so here it is, but now in full 60fps. You'll appreciate the full frame-rate - this flickers so badly that you can't see what's happening half the time at only 30!
__________________
No cheats were used in the making of this video.
